    "body": "From https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/pull/10241#pullrequestreview-526581636: I think there should be just one top-level try...catch block around everything in the CLI interface that catches exceptions not properly handled below, reports any diagnostic info it finds and exits. Currently there are multiple ad-hoc try...catch with very limited scope that look as if they were going to handle errors but all they don't actually do anything, they just report and exit and that should be delegated to the top level.",
