    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If we're afraid to break tooling too much like that, I'd write a thin wrapper script that covers the most commonly used old command line options and translates them to the new options, but with a \"use-at-your-own-peril\" plus \"better-update-your-stuff\" policy...\r\nBut yeah, I'm not sure we'll be able to agree on this and if we want to consider it, we'd probably need a draft of how the simple CLI to StandardJSON translation would look like in practice to decide if it is likely to increase the usage learning curve too much or not.",
