    "body": "If I read that the main attachment is towards non-standard-json output options of the CLI. Actually I agree that we should keep those... or put differently: I would keep ``--standard-json`` as CLI option anyways, meaning proper json input and output - but if the compiler is instead invoked using the \"simple translation of CLI options to standard-json\" I also wouldn't output standard-json, but rather just plainly output the requested output components. And we could keep ``--combined-json`` to pack the output like that instead... but yeah, granted: things get a bit fuzzy there, I hadn't thought this through entirely...",
